      "writtenOn": "2020-03-02T14:48:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Heh well this is not what |drm_atomic| is, for sure; atomic refers to being \nable to commit a new set of DRM properties, e.g. planes, formats, configurations,\natomically (whereas before user code had to configure and commit one step at\nat time, unwinding the committed actions if anything failed). \n\nMaybe what we could do in this CL is:\na) Rename this |drm_atomic| to |video_overlays{_supported}|, to better \n represent what it means.  Usage is not widespread: \n https://source.chromium.org/search?q\u003dsrc%2Fplatform%2F%20drm_atomic\u0026ss\u003dchromiumos\nb) Remove the proposed |amd64_video_overlays|\nc) in the follow up CL, use the |video_overlays{_supported}|.\n\nWDYT?",
